Step 1: Extract the sowing number plots from the field data

metadata2 <- read.table("~/Desktop/POSTDOC_2020/1_MAIN_PROJECT_ESCHIKON/7_Phenotyping/4_picture_field/metadata_sn_plots.txt", sep = "\t", header = T)
metadata2 <- metadata2 %>%
  group_by(HOST, plot) %>%
  tally()

#Full collection metadata Eschikon (Daniel and Cecile sequencing)
matrix_host_phenotypes <- merge(metadata_full, metadata2)
matrix_host_phenotypes2 <- matrix_host_phenotypes[,c(11,12)]

matrix_host_phenotypes2$HOST = as.factor(matrix_host_phenotypes2$HOST) 
levels(matrix_host_phenotypes2$HOST)

Step 2: Create a 0/1 matrix per host (here an example with the cultivar Arobase) with a radom sub-sampling of the samples found on other hosts

arobase <- matrix_host_phenotypes2 %>% 
  filter(HOST == "AROBASE")
#AROBASE$pheno <- 1
tmp_sub <- matrix_host_phenotypes2 %>% 
  filter(HOST != "AROBASE")
#select random sample of three rows from data frame
X <- tmp_sub$gvcf_name
rand_df <- as.data.frame(lapply(1:100, function(i) sample(X, size = 100))) %>%
  setNames(paste0("V", 1:100))
rand_df$ID <- rownames(rand_df)
rand_df$ID <- as.factor(rand_df$ID)
#melt:
data_long <- gather(rand_df, HOST, gvcf_name, V1:V100, factor_key=TRUE)
#matrix:

done

names(voi) = c("chr", "ps", "ref", "alt", "score", "effect", "target_type","target", "ANN")

# Annotations from Lapalu et al 2023:
annotations <- read.delim("~/Desktop/AMBIZIONE_2022/0_raw_data_parental_strains_genomes/IPO323/Lapalu_annotation2023/z.tritici.IPO323.annotations.txt", header = T, sep = "\t", na.strings = "")


### grouped plot with 1% of SNPs
Varobase <- read.csv("~/Desktop/POSTDOC_2020/1_MAIN_PROJECT_ESCHIKON/8_GWAS/8_host_gwas/2_subsampling_gwas/arobase/arobase2_top1perc/summarized_top1perc_SNPs_complete_arobase_filtered.csv", header = T, sep = "\t")
Varobase <- Varobase[,c(-14)]
names(Varobase)[names(Varobase) == 'V100'] <- 'Subsampling'

thresholdArobase = 0.05/951427

Varobase1 <- Varobase %>% 
  # Compute chromosome size
  group_by(chr) %>% 
  summarise(chr_len=max(ps)) %>% 
  # Calculate cumulative position of each chromosome
  mutate(tot=cumsum(chr_len)-chr_len) %>%
  dplyr::select(-chr_len) %>%
  # Add this info to the initial dataset
  left_join(Varobase, ., by=c("chr"="chr")) %>%
  # Add a cumulative position of each SNP
  arrange(chr, ps) %>%
  mutate(BPcum=ps+tot)

Varobase1 <- Varobase1 %>% 
  # Add highlight and annotation information
  mutate( is_highlight=ifelse(-log10(p_wald)>thresholdArobase, "yes", "no"))

customHighlight <- Varobase1 %>%
  filter(is_highlight == "yes") %>%
  group_by(chr)

axisdf <- Varobase1 %>% 
  group_by(chr) %>% 
  filter(chr < 14) %>%
  summarise(center=(min(BPcum)+max(BPcum))/2) 
axisdf2 <- axisdf %>% 
  summarise((size = center*2))
## Warning: Returning more (or less) than 1 row per `summarise()` group was deprecated in
## dplyr 1.1.0.
## â¹ Please use `reframe()` instead.
## â¹ When switching from `summarise()` to `reframe()`, remember that `reframe()`
##   always returns an ungrouped data frame and adjust accordingly.
## Call `lifecycle::last_lifecycle_warnings()` to see where this warning was
## generated.
arobase_peak <- Varobase1%>%filter(p_wald < thresholdArobase)%>%filter(chr < 14)
arobase_peak <- left_join(arobase_peak, voi)
## Joining with `by = join_by(chr, ps)`
arobase_peak <- left_join(arobase_peak, annotations)
## Joining with `by = join_by(target)`
arobase_peak$HOST <- "AROBASE"
arobase_best <- arobase_peak %>% group_by(chr, gene,MPI_genes, start,end, HOST) %>% tally() %>%filter(n>1)
arobase_best2 <- left_join(arobase_best, arobase_peak)
## Joining with `by = join_by(chr, gene, MPI_genes, start, end, HOST)`
ggplot(Varobase1%>%filter(chr < 14), aes(x=BPcum, y=-log10(p_wald))) +

 new_scale_colour() +
